"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901347","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-17","<p>The department is not aware of potentially anti-competitive practises. Revenue allocation arrangements are a matter for Rail Settlement Plan Ltd and individual bus operators.</p><p>As the UK’s independent competition regulator it is for the Competition and Markets Authority to investigate anti-competitive practices and details of how to raise concerns with the CMA can be found on their website. The independent rail regulator, the Office of Rail and Road, also has a role in this area under its concurrent competition powers.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","142868","2018-05-17T16:03:16.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901347/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901347/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901347/answer","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901347/answer/previousversion/58119","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-10","East Midlands Trains","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the apportioning of ticket revenues and cross-subsidy arrangements between Stagecoach companies Megabus and East Midlands Trains for the provision of travel on the East Midlands Trains route.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","142867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901348","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-17","<p>The department is not aware of potentially anti-competitive practises. Revenue allocation arrangements are a matter for Rail Settlement Plan Ltd and individual bus operators.</p><p>As the UK’s independent competition regulator it is for the Competition and Markets Authority to investigate anti-competitive practices and details of how to raise concerns with the CMA can be found on their website. The independent rail regulator, the Office of Rail and Road, also has a role in this area under its concurrent competition powers.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","142867","2018-05-17T16:03:17.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901348/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901348/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901348/answer","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901348/answer/previousversion/58120","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-10","East Midlands Trains","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to instruct the Competition and Markets Authority to investigate potentially anti-competitive practices by Stagecoach companies Megabus and East Midlands Trains for the provision of travel on the East Midlands Trains route.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","142868"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901349","Cabinet Office","false","2018-05-16","<p>The Government is committed to the principles of transparency and openness across the public sector.</p><p>We continually keep the scope of the Freedom of Information Act under review.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-05-16T09:20:07.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901349/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901349/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901349/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-05-10","Freedom of Information: Private Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether he intends to hold a consultation on extending the Freedom of Information Act 2001 to private sector providers of public services.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","142762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901350","Cabinet Office","false","2018-05-17","<p>The Government has noted that this is one of the recommendations in the latest report on ethical standards in outsourced public services published earlier this month by the Committee on Standards in Public Life (CSPL).</p><p> </p><p>We will make our formal response to the Committee in due course.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-05-17T16:13:38.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901350/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901350/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901350/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-05-10","Government Departments: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether he plans to require Government suppliers to publish (a) their processes for dealing with and (b) anonymised outcomes of whistleblowing cases and complaints as a condition of entering into contracts with Government.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","142763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901351","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-17","<p>All criminal courts have access to video links and we are increasing the availability of video links across the civil and family courts. Combined, around 90% of courts have this technology.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-05-17T16:39:48.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901351/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901351/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901351/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-10","Courts: Video Conferencing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the percentage of courts which currently have the technological capacity to host video links.","false","Biography information for Holly Lynch","Halifax","Holly Lynch","142894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901352","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-17","<p>NHS Sunderland Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG) as lead commissioner, and Newcastle Gateshead CCG as associate to the contract, have recently conducted a full service review to identify areas for improvement and ensure sustainability for the future. The review was completed in consultation with the current provider, Northumberland, Tyne and Wear NHS Foundation Trust (NTW).</p><p> </p><p>The current contract for the service is due to expire on 30 June 2018, following this the CCG expects to retain a contract with NTW from 1 July 2018 which will continue to provide services for patients with severe head injuries, the group for whom the service was originally established. Patients who have a minor or mild head injury will be treated in more suitable local community services.</p><p> </p><p>Commissioners intend to review these services over the coming months, and look forward to engaging with patients and other stakeholders as part of this work.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-05-17T15:22:55.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901352/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901352/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901352/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-10","Sunderland and Gateshead Community Acquired Brain Injury Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the effect of the closure of the Community Acquired Brain Injury Service on patients in (a) Sunderland and (b) Gateshead.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","142801"
