"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901366","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-17","<p>The Government collects quarterly and annual statistics on how many people approach local authorities as homeless in England, including if they are vulnerable as a result of having served in HM forces. The latest local authority level statistics, and quarterly statistics since 2009, can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-homelessness" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-homelessness</a></p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak","142828","2018-05-17T14:41:19.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901366/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901366/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901366/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-10","Homelessness: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many veterans of the armed forces are classed as homeless in each constituent part of the UK.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","142827"
