"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901368","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-05-17","<p>Around 240 Ministry of Defence civil servants have been allocated an official car to enable them to carry out essential duties including security, welfare, chaplaincy, safety, training and recruitment. Over 200 are security service engineers who provide security services to all of Government and the Royal palaces. The cars are held by the individual until the conclusion of their tenure in the role. Their grades are primarily bands D(EO), C2((HEO) and C1(SEO), and skill zone equivalents.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-05-17T16:35:58.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901368/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901368/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901368/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-05-10","Ministry of Defence: Official Cars","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 10 May 2018 to Question 141014, on Official Cars, what the total number of civil servants who have been provided with a car to carry out duties is; and what the pay grade is of each of those civil servants.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","142818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901369","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-17","<p>The Government is strongly committed to the Armed Forces Covenant and has taken significant action to ensure that serving personnel and veterans do not face any disadvantage as a result of their brave service for this country. That is why we are working closely with the Ministry of Defence as part of our cross-government Rough Sleeping and Homelessness Reduction Taskforce to achieve our commitment of halving rough sleeping by 2022 and eliminating it by 2027.</p><p>In addition, as part of the Homelessness Reduction Act, the duty to refer will ensure that armed forces personnel leaving the service, who are at risk of homelessness, are referred to a local authority for support.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-05-17T14:27:56.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901369/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901369/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/901369/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-10","Homelessness: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what support his Department provides to veterans who have left the armed forces and become homeless.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","142829"
